⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 62/120 – Latest Salary Per Employee

🎤 Interview Question

Each employee can have multiple salary revisions.

Write PySpark code to return only the latest salary record for each employee.


---

📊 Input Dataset

emp_id	salary	effective_date

101	50000	2023-01-01
101	60000	2024-01-01
102	45000	2023-06-01
102	52000	2024-02-01
103	70000	2024-03-01



---

✅ Expected Output

emp_id	salary	effective_date

101	60000	2024-01-01
102	52000	2024-02-01
103	70000	2024-03-01



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.window import Window
from pyspark.sql.functions import row_number, col

window_spec = (
    Window.partitionBy("emp_id")
          .orderBy(col("effective_date").desc())
)

result = (
    df.withColumn("rn", row_number().over(window_spec))
      .filter(col("rn") == 1)
      .drop("rn")
)

result.show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. Why not use groupBy().max(effective_date)?

Answer

groupBy().max() only returns the latest date.

It does not return the corresponding salary or other columns.


---

Q2. Why is row_number() the preferred solution?

Answer

Because it returns the entire latest row, not just the maximum date.


---

Q3. Is this question common?

Answer

Yes. It is one of the most frequently asked PySpark and SQL interview problems.


